ironment, as well as the vehicle, for the expression of a world-orientation—in a situation where open discourse was inconceivable. The book is based on extensive interviews, musical recordings, photographs and scholarly analyses. It is unique in its choice of communities, its wealth of original documents, and its novel interpretation of sound. Writing on Water is creative non-fiction. The presentation is evocative and poetic, but at the same time it transmits knowledge. The book can aid research and serve in courses in philosophy, religion, music, ethnomusicology, anthropology, aesthetics, Jewish studies, folklore, oral history, and performance studies. It is also a work of art and literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aCommunism-Europe, Central-History-20th century. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)-Europe, Central. 0aJews-Europe, Central-Interviews. 0aJews-Europe, Central-Music. 0aJudaism-Europe, Central-Customs and practices. 0aJudaism-Sudy and teaching-Europe, Central. 0aMusic-Performance-Europe, Central-20th century. 0aOral tradition-Europe, Central. 0aOrthodox Judaism-Europe, Central-History-20th century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aAnthropology, Budapest, Communism, Folklore, Jewish studies, Jews, Music, Prague, Religion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2018z978311078052940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789633862582423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789633862582/original  a978-3-11-078052-9  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles